message.entry: In expressions of the form T.X = B where T is a tall table, B must be a tall array.
Creating tall tables using indexing expressions is not supported.
Deleting all variables of a tall table using expressions of the form T.{0} = [] is not supported.
Deleting row names of a tall table is not supported.
Expressions of the form T(:,:) = [] are not allowed for tall table T.
tall table does not support deleting only portions of a variable.
When indexing a tall table, the first subscript must be either a tall array or ':'.
Tall table row subscripts must be real positive integers or logicals.
A tall {0} can only be concatenated with another tall {0}.
Setting row names of a tall table is not supported.
Setting all variables of a tall table using expressions of the form T.{0} = B is not supported.
Indexed assignments of the form T'{'...,...'}' = B are not supported for tall tables.
Indexed assignments of the form T(...,...) = B are not supported for tall {0}.
Indexing a tall table using row names is not supported.
When indexing a tall table using vartype all variables must have known type.
